Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Production date: 152 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Pausanias. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX L167.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0966)
